<!-- <head> is ignored - only its children are copied into the output page head. -->
<!--
    GramFrame plugin loader for the Oxygen WebHelp Responsive template.

    Loading gramframe.bundle.js upgrades every <table class="gram-config"> on
    the page into an interactive spectrogram viewer; it no-ops on pages that
    have none. The gram-config class arrives from the DITA outputclass that
    generate_dita.py emits, which Oxygen passes through to the HTML @class.

    The bundle ships beside this fragment under resources/gramframe.bundle.js;
    Oxygen's custom-resources fileset copies resources/** into the output at
    ${oxygen-webhelp-assets-dir}/template/resources/, so the src below mirrors
    the path convention the template's other custom scripts already use.

    Pin this bundle to the SAME GramFrame release as scripts/vendor/gramframe/
    (see resources/VERSION) so the Oxygen production output and the
    publish_html.py dev preview render grams identically.

    Persistence shim (GramFrame >= v0.1.10): the bundle persists annotations to
    localStorage (not ephemeral sessionStorage) only when the page has an element
    with the literal id "gf-persistent". generate_dita.py stamps that id on the
    instructor-only edition marker, but DITA-OT/Oxygen topic-scope every element
    id ("gram_01__gf-persistent"), so getElementById would miss it. We can't
    post-process Oxygen output, so the inline script below normalises the
    topic-prefixed id back to the bare literal client-side, before the deferred
    bundle's DOMContentLoaded init runs (the non-deferred inline script registers
    its listener first). It is keyed off the .edition-instructor marker, which the
    trainee DITAVAL strips from the student build, so student pages get neither
    the id nor persistence. publish_html.py does the same rewrite statically for
    the dev preview (normalize_persistence_marker). Keep the two in sync.
-->
<head xmlns:whc="http://www.oxygenxml.com/webhelp/components" whc:version="22.0">
    <script>
        document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function () {
            if (document.getElementById("gf-persistent")) { return; }
            var marker = document.querySelector(".edition-instructor");
            if (marker) { marker.id = "gf-persistent"; }
        });
    </script>
    <script defer="defer"
        src="${oxygen-webhelp-assets-dir}/template/resources/gramframe.bundle.js?buildId=${oxygen-webhelp-build-number}"></script>
</head>
